## 13. Verify the Contract on Polygonscan

### Automatic verification

Set:

```dotenv
AUTO_VERIFY=true
POLYGONSCAN_API_KEY=YOUR_API_KEY
```

Then deploy normally:

```bash
npx hardhat run --network polygonAmoyTestnet scripts/deploy_x402.js
```

### Manual verification

Run:

```bash
npx hardhat verify \
  --network polygonAmoyTestnet \
  CONTRACT_ADDRESS \
  ADMIN_WALLET_ADDRESS
```

Example:

```bash
npx hardhat verify \
  --network polygonAmoyTestnet \
  0x1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef12345678 \
  0xabcdefabcdefabcdefabcdefabcdefabcdefabcd
```

Verification requires:

```text
matching Solidity compiler version
matching optimizer settings
matching constructor arguments
matching source code
matching linked libraries, when any exist
```

## 14. Perform Post-Deployment Validation

Do not consider deployment complete until the following checks pass.

### Check contract bytecode

Open the contract address on the network explorer and confirm that deployed bytecode exists.

Using Hardhat console:

```bash
npx hardhat console --network polygonAmoyTestnet
```

```javascript
const code = await ethers.provider.getCode("CONTRACT_ADDRESS");
code !== "0x";
```

### Check the configured administrator

Load the deployed contract:

```javascript
const contract = await ethers.getContractAt(
  "X402Splitter",
  "CONTRACT_ADDRESS"
);
```

Call the administrator getter defined by the contract, for example:

```javascript
await contract.admin();
```

The exact getter name must match the Solidity contract.

### Test a small payment

Before integrating the contract with the Rust application:

1. Use a test video invoice.
2. Generate a signed authorization payload.
3. Submit a very small test payment.
4. Confirm that the expected `Paid` event is emitted.
5. Confirm creator and administrator balances.
6. Confirm the backend recognizes the invoice.
7. Confirm the buyer receives video access.

## 15. Configure the Rust Application

After successful deployment, update the backend environment:

```dotenv
X402_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0xDEPLOYED_CONTRACT_ADDRESS
X402_CHAIN_ID=80002
X402_RPC_HTTP=https://YOUR_AMOY_HTTP_RPC
X402_RPC_WSS=wss://YOUR_AMOY_WEBSOCKET_RPC
X402_ADMIN_PRIVKEY=0xBACKEND_AUTHORIZATION_SIGNER_PRIVATE_KEY
```

The contract administrator address and the backend signing key must follow the authorization model implemented by the Solidity contract.

Restart the Rust application after changing environment variables.

## 16. Docker-Based Deployment

The project also supports deployment through Docker Compose.

### Testnet deployment

```bash
docker compose run --rm x402-deployer \
  npx hardhat run \
  --network polygonAmoyTestnet \
  scripts/deploy_x402.js
```

The previous guidance mentioned `megaTestnet`, but that network is not currently defined in `hardhat.config.js`. Do not use `megaTestnet` until its network configuration has been added.

### Gas estimation through Docker

```bash
docker compose run --rm x402-deployer \
  npx hardhat run \
  --network polygonAmoyTestnet \
  scripts/estimate_gas_cost.js
```

Ensure the container receives environment variables. Common approaches include:

```text
Docker Compose env_file
Docker Compose environment entries
shell environment variables
secret management integration
```

## 17. Polygon Mainnet Preparation

Mainnet deployment is currently disabled in `hardhat.config.js` because the `polygonMainnet` network block is commented out.

Enable it only after testnet validation is complete:

```javascript
polygonMainnet: {
  url: POLYGON_RPC_HTTP || "https://polygon-rpc.com",
  chainId: Number(POLYGON_CHAIN_ID || 137),
  accounts: PRIVATE_KEY ? [PRIVATE_KEY] : []
}
```

Mainnet `.env` example:

```dotenv
PRIVATE_KEY=0xDEDICATED_MAINNET_DEPLOYER_PRIVATE_KEY
ADMIN_WALLET=0xPRODUCTION_MULTISIG_ADDRESS
POLYGON_RPC_HTTP=https://YOUR_PRODUCTION_POLYGON_RPC
POLYGON_CHAIN_ID=137
POLYGONSCAN_API_KEY=YOUR_POLYGONSCAN_API_KEY
CONFIRMATIONS=5
AUTO_VERIFY=true
```

Estimate gas before mainnet deployment:

```bash
npx hardhat run --network polygonMainnet scripts/estimate_gas_cost.js
```

Deploy:

```bash
npx hardhat run --network polygonMainnet scripts/deploy_x402.js
```

Docker version:

```bash
docker compose run --rm x402-deployer \
  npx hardhat run \
  --network polygonMainnet \
  scripts/deploy_x402.js
```

